##### MF3: REACTION CROSS SECTIONS                                2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
All the data present in the following MT-sections have been       2522 1451
calculated with TALYS, possibly normalized to experimental data.  2522 1451
If the maximal cross section in an excitation function over the   2522 1451
whole energy range does not exceed 1.e-9 b, the MT-number is not  2522 1451
included. Cross sections lower than 1.e-20 b are assumed to have  2522 1451
no physical meaning and are set to zero. All MT numbers extend up 2522 1451
to the highest incident energy.                                   2522 1451
The following reaction channels/MT numbers are generally included:2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
- MT1      : Total cross section                                  2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
Calculated with the optical model over the whole energy range,    2522 1451
or partly reproduced using experimental data.                     2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
- MT2      : Elastic scattering cross section                     2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
Obtained by subtracting the non-elastic cross section from the    2522 1451
total cross section.                                              2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
- MT3      : Non-elastic cross section                            2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
Calculated with the optical model over the whole energy range.    2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
- MT4      : Total inelastic cross section                        2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
Sum of MT=51-91.                                                  2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
- MT5      : (n,anything) cross section                           2522 1451
                                                                  2522 1451
MT5 contains the reactions which can not be stored in any other   2522 1451
MT-number. The information of MF3/MT5 can be combined with        2522 1451
MF6/MT5 to obtain residual production cross sections particle     2522 1451
production cross sections and (double-)differential cross         2522 1451
sections.                                                         2522 1451
